//======Java Script Execution Context=========
 JS runs the program in two phases
 1: Global Execution Context -> it stored in variable named 'this'. but in brouser the value of 'this' is window object.
    it execute under the thread. JS is a single threaded, inside that all this is process.
	
 2: Function Execution Context ->	
 
 3: Eval Execution Context (in mongoos) -> property of Global object
	
Example:
    let val1 = 10
    let val2 = 5
	function addNumber(num1, num2){
	  let total = num1 + num2
	  return total
	}
	let result1=addNumber(val1,val2)
	let result2=addNumber(10,2)
	
JS runs the program in two phases
	
	a:  Global Execution -> this
	
	b: Memory Creation Phase / Creation Phase - In this phase the memory location for variables is allocated. 
	   val1 -> undefined
	   val2 -> undefined
	   addNumber -> definition -> (num1, num2){
	                          let total = num1 + num2
	                          return total
	   result1 -> undefined
	   result2 -> undefined
	
	c: Execution Phase - line no 11:  val1 = 10
	                     line no 12: val2 = 5
						 line no 17: addNumber = create own new execution context, it will create 'new variable environment' and 'execution phase'. 
						                         In each and every function execution it will create. Than it will go again in memory phase and execution phases for 'addNumber'.
									memory phase = val1 -> undefined
									               val2 -> undefined
												   total -> undefined
									execution phase = num1 -> 10
                                                      num2 -> 5
													  total -> 15  // this total's value return in the Global Execution part
													  
												After complete its execution , new execution context will be deleted.
												
